04/04/85 dmpr_unlock_pv

Syntax as a command:  dmpr_unlock_pv pvname -control_arg


Function:  unlocks a physical volume for volume dumping should the
dumper process terminate abnormally with the lock set.  A control
argument must be used to specify the dump mode that is locked.


Arguments:
pvname
   is the name of the physical volume that was locked.


Control arguments:
-complete, -comp
   unlocks the complete dump mode.
-consolidated, -cons
   unlocks the consolidated dump mode.
-incremental, -incr
   unlocks the incremental dump mode.


Access required:  This command requires hc_backup_ access.
